Ala.\nSend me (1) 8-page illustrated booklet, \u2018The\nStory of an Opportunity at. Home/' (2) Infor\nmation about Alabama Power Co. Preferred\nStock, (3) Details of Easy Payment Plan.\nName\nAddress\n_L_______\nu\n\nCITY IS TAKING UP\nSiege Guns May Be Brought\nto City for Installation\nin Parks\nBirmingham is not going to throw away\nher chance to get a part of the siege\nguns and howitzers declared obsolete by\nthe war department.\nA limited quantity of this condemned\nordnance equipment was offered to the\ncity several days ago. The American De\ntable in the city clerk's office for two\nweeks, when it will be adopted pro\nviding there Is no opposition. The next\nstep will then be to flv the date of the\nelection when the bond issue is to be\ndecided by a vote of the qualified elec\ntors. The city council has also fixed\nJuly 26 as the date for beginning a\nclean-up campaign, it being the inten\ntion of the authorities to give Meridian\nsuch a cleaning as the city has never\nhad before. In this work the Board of\nTrade, Rotary Club and other organiza\ntions have pledged hearty co-operation.\nFollowing a discussion of general\nsanitary conditions, a movement has\ndeveloped for the early extension of the\nsanitary sewerage system to all parts\nof Meridian at a cost of approximately\n$50,000, the money to be raised by bond\nIssue on a vote of the people. During\nthe discussion of general health con\nditions by members of the council, City\nHealth Officer T. J. Houston and\nCounty Health Officer W. A. Carpen\nter, it developed that there are some\nthing like 900 surface closets in the\ncity, which covers that territory not\nreached by the sewerage system. It\nwas stated that during the warm sea\nson these closets are a menace to the\ngood health of Meridan and the abol\nishment of this situation by extension\nof the sewer plant will be pushed.\nIt has been officially announced that\nC. L. Bunch of Sheffield. Ala., has been\nappointed to succeed Horace M. Little\nof Meridian as master mechanic of the\nSouthern railway\u2019s New Orleans and\nNortheastern shops here Mr. Little\nresigned to accept the presidency and\ngeneral managership of the Buffalo\nSulphur Refining Company of Creede,\nCol., his headquarters to be in Denver.\nThe county democratic executive\ncommittee has been called to meet here\nat the courthouse Saturday. July 17, at\n10 a. m. for the purpose of organiza\ntion by the election of officers, after\nwhich all preliminary steps will be\ntaken for holding the congressional\nelection August 17, and the special elec\ntion for c.ircuit judge at the same time.\nOn the opening date of the county\nschools, September 6. marked improve\nments will be noted in school buildings,\ngrounds, etc., over past conditions.\nImprovement work under the supervis\nion of County Superintendent of Edu\ncation Riddell and J. T. Calhoun, su\npervisor of rural schools, is now well\nunder way.\nAugust has been fixed as the date\nhere for the first sales of tobacco raised\nin this county and immediate section.\nThe Lauderdale County Tobacco Grow\ners\u2019 Association, which will have charge\nof the sales, has already been assured\nthat a number of buyers from manu\nfacturing establishments will be pres\nent to bid on the weed. Instructions\nare being sent out to growers as to the\nbest way to handle their crops for the\nmarket.\nWhenever Von Need a General\nStrengthening Tonic\nTake the Old Standard GROVES\nTASTELESS chill TONNIC. It Strength\nens and Builds Up the System by Puri\nfying and Enriching the Blood. You\ncan soon feel its Strengthening, In\nvigorating effect. 60c.\u2014Adv.\nSAY \u201cDIAMOND DYES\u201d\nDon\u2019t streak or ruin yonr material In\na poor dye. Insist on \u201cDiamond Dyes.\u201d\nEasy directions in every package.\n-t- T\"T t t t T-tf t 9 (ulus\nj GIRLS! LEMONS\nj BLEACH; WHITEN j\nI I\n1\n1 Make Lemon Lotion to Double\nBeauty of Your Skin\nSqueeze the Juice of two lemons Into\na bottle containing three ounces of